{"abstract":[{"text":"A 2D convex polygon shape used for physics collision.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ConvexPolygonShape2D","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A 2D convex polygon shape, intended for use in physics. Used internally in ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D","isActive":true},{"text":" when it’s in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids"},{"text":" mode.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"solid","type":"text"}]},{"text":", which means it detects collisions from objects that are fully inside it, unlike ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape2D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" which is hollow. This makes it more suitable for both detection and physics."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Convex decomposition:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" A concave polygon can be split up into several convex polygons. This allows dynamic physics bodies to have complex concave collisions (at a performance cost) and can be achieved by using several "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" nodes or by using the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" node in "},{"code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" mode. To generate a collision polygon from a sprite, select the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Sprite2D","isActive":true},{"text":" node, go to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sprite2D","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" menu that appears above the viewport, and choose "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create Polygon2D Sibling"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is faster to check collisions against compared to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape2D","isActive":true},{"text":", but it is slower than primitive collision shapes such as ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CircleShape2D"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RectangleShape2D"},{"type":"text","text":". Its use should generally be limited to medium-sized objects that cannot have their collision accurately represented by primitive shapes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/points"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/setPointCloud(_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/